sub: NPV & IRR — Discounted Cash Flow
text: At a 10% discount rate the project creates QAR 4.1M of value.

metric: NPV @ 10% | value: 4.1M | unit: QAR | trend: up
metric: IRR | value: 37.6% | target: 10% WACC
metric: WACC | value: 10%
metric: Profitability index | value: 2.1x

| DCF (QAR '000) | Y0 | Y1 | Y2 | Y3 | Y4 | Y5 |
| Free cash flow | (3,800) | 964 | 1,338 | 2,202 | 3,088 | 3,390 |
| Discount factor | 1.00 | 0.91 | 0.83 | 0.75 | 0.68 | 0.62 |
| Discounted FCF | (3,800) | 876 | 1,106 | 1,654 | 2,109 | 2,105 |

info: Cost of capital — WACC of 10% = risk-free 4.5% + β 1.0 × equity premium 5.5%. IRR of 38% sits far above the 10% hurdle and a 15–18% GCC manufacturing benchmark. | type: info

sub: Break-even Analysis
text: Break-even at ~26% utilisation — well below the Year-1 plan of 38%.

metric: BE utilisation | value: ~26%
metric: BE revenue | value: QAR 2.5M
metric: Contribution margin | value: 58%
metric: Y1 margin of safety | value: 31%

| Year-1 cost structure | QAR | Basis |
| Fixed costs (OPEX + dep + fixed COGS) | 1,465,190 | Year 1 |
| Contribution margin | 58% | 1 − variable cost % |
| Break-even revenue | 2,531,427 | fixed ÷ CM |
| Break-even utilisation | 26% | of 500 t capacity |

info: Resilience — with Year-1 revenue of QAR 3.67M against a break-even of QAR 2.5M, the project carries a 31% margin of safety from the first year. | type: success

sub: Sensitivity & Scenarios
text: Each scenario is a live re-run of the model. Revenue is the dominant driver; the project stays viable across all cases.

| Scenario | Assumption | IRR | NPV (QAR M) | Verdict |
| Base case | As projected | 38% | 4.1 | Go |
| Revenue +10% | Faster ramp / premium mix | 46% | 5.4 | Upside |
| Revenue −10% | Slower adoption | 29% | 2.7 | Viable |
| RM cost +10% | Pigment price spike | 34% | 3.4 | Viable |
| No export | Domestic only | 15% | 0.6 | Downside |

- Revenue (price × volume) is the dominant driver of returns.
- Raw-material cost is a moderate driver — managed by dual sourcing and price locks.
- Export accelerates returns; the domestic-only case is the key downside to watch.
- Every scenario clears the 10% cost of capital with a positive NPV.

sub: Financial Verdict
info: FINANCIALLY VIABLE — PROCEED. IRR of 38% versus a 10% hurdle. NPV of QAR 4.1M. Payback in ~2.7 years. Margins expand with scale, the project is debt-free, and it breaks even at only 26% of capacity. | type: success

| Finding | Interpretation |
| NPV QAR 4.1M | Positive at the 10% cost of capital — creates shareholder value. |
| IRR 38% | Far above the GCC manufacturing hurdle of 15–18%. |
| Payback 2.7 yrs | Capital recovered during Year 3 — excellent for manufacturing. |
| Zero debt | 100% equity — no leverage risk or covenants. |
| Break-even 26% | Large buffer against slower-than-planned market adoption. |

break:

section: 05. Risk

sub: Risk Matrix
text: Principal risks scored by likelihood and impact, each with a mitigation.

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
| Slow market adoption | Medium | High | Lead-time & service edge; pilot accounts |
| Raw-material price spike | Medium | Medium | Dual sourcing, 90-day buffer, price locks |
| Export execution delay | Medium | High | Early distributor search; SASO/ESMA registration |
| Colour-consistency failure | Low | High | ISO 9001, ΔE<2 control, senior chemist |
| Key-person dependency | Medium | Medium | Document formulations; train a deputy |
| Permitting delay | Low | Medium | Manateq streamlined approvals; early filing |

break:

section: 06. Implementation

sub: Implementation Timeline
text: Roughly 12 months from equity confirmation to commercial launch (Q1 2027).

| Phase | Months | Key activities |
| Setup & approvals | 0–3 | CR, MOCI, lease signing, civil-defence & environmental permits |
| Civil works & fit-out | 2–6 | Building works, solvent room, electrical & utilities |
| Equipment install | 5–9 | Dispersers, mills, filling line, lab — install & commission |
| Recruitment & training | 6–10 | Hire chemist & team; formulation & QC training |
| Trial production & QC | 9–11 | Pilot batches; ISO 9001 audit; customer samples |
| Commercial launch | 12 | First commercial orders — Q1 2027 |

break:

section: 07. Recommendation

info: RECOMMENDATION: PROCEED WITH INVESTMENT. Medad Ink Factory is a strategically compelling, financially strong and operationally manageable project. It establishes Qatar's first ink manufacturer, substitutes QAR 18.8M of annual imports, and returns an IRR of ~38% on a QAR 3.80M equity outlay. | type: success

| Dimension | Verdict |
| Strategic | First-mover, import-substituting, Vision-2030 aligned, export-capable. |
| Market | QAR 18.8M domestic + USD 185M GCC; no local competitor. |
| Technical | Proven process, German-grade equipment, ISO 9001 quality, lean team. |
| Financial | NPV QAR 4.1M · IRR 38% · payback 2.7 yrs · debt-free. |
| Risk | No single risk threatens viability; dominant risks are management-controllable. |

sub: Defined Terms
def: NPV | meaning: Net Present Value — discounted value the project creates above its cost of capital.
def: IRR | meaning: Internal Rate of Return — the discount rate at which NPV equals zero.
def: WACC | meaning: Weighted Average Cost of Capital — the project's 10% hurdle rate.
def: TAM | meaning: Total Addressable Market — QAR 18.8M of annual Qatari raw-ink demand.
def: HS 3215 | meaning: Customs tariff code for printing inks, writing or drawing ink.
